    <summaries>
      <summary>
        <versionCode>00</versionCode>
        <actionDate>2006-04-04</actionDate>
        <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
        <updateDate>2006-05-08T20:13:12Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p>Staff Sergeant Carlos Farler Citizen Soldier Equality Act of 2006 - Requires that, in the case of a reserve member of the Armed Forces who is retired due to disability incurred as a result of being wounded in action, or whose name is placed on the temporary disability retired list because of a disability incurred for which the member is awarded the Purple Heart, such member shall be credited with the same number of years of service that would be credited to a member of the regular (non-reserve) Armed Forces for such service.</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
    <title>Staff Sergeant Carlos Farler Citizen Soldier Equality Act of 2006</title>
